You can use this regular expression to extract the three character code from a filename in the format "57-1Jn.usfm": 
```regex
\b(\d{3}[A-Za-z]*)\.(?:USFM)$
```
This will match any string that starts with 3 digits, followed by zero or more uppercase or lowercase letters or digits (represented as [A-Za-z0-9]), and ends with ".usfm". The `\b` is a word boundary to ensure the code comes before the extension.
